  "text": "The withdrawal reflexes of the muscles peroneus longus and brevis (PER) and extensor digitorum longus (EDL) were chosen for manipulation, because their receptive fields exhibit little variation across normal rats [CITATION_1] Holmberg and Schouenborg, 1996a,b) . Also, these muscles have long tendons that can be transferred to new positions at birth.",
